* Love and marriage *

00:20.969 --> 00:22.734
* Go together like *

00:22.769 --> 00:25.200
* A horse and carriage *

00:25.235 --> 00:29.200
* This I tell ya, brother *

00:29.235 --> 00:31.133
* You can't have one *

00:31.168 --> 00:34.033
* Without the other *

00:34.068 --> 00:38.934
* Love and marriage *

00:38.969 --> 00:40.334
* It's an institute *

00:40.369 --> 00:42.734
* You can't disparage *

00:42.769 --> 00:46.501
* Ask the local gentry *

00:46.536 --> 00:51.067
* And they will say
It's elementary *

00:51.102 --> 00:55.868
* Try, try, try
To separate them *

00:55.903 --> 00:59.567
* It's an illusion *

00:59.602 --> 01:04.700
* Try, try, try
And you will only come *

01:04.736 --> 01:08.133
* To this conclusion *

01:08.168 --> 01:10.234
* Love and marriage **

01:18.033 --> 01:20.901
Al, come on down!
It's time for work!

01:24.400 --> 01:25.901
Come on, honey.

01:25.936 --> 01:28.901
I'm making you
a nice, hot breakfast.

01:28.936 --> 01:32.400
Just listen
to that bacon sizzle.

01:35.903 --> 01:37.300
Keep it hot, Peg.

01:37.335 --> 01:38.801
I'll be down
in a minute.

01:38.836 --> 01:40.501
Sure, I will.

01:40.536 --> 01:42.501
Peggy, I've got
some great news.

01:42.536 --> 01:45.000
Two men came
to our house-

01:45.035 --> 01:47.000
Al, I'm going
over to Marcie's!

01:47.035 --> 01:48.367
They're gone now.

01:50.601 --> 01:52.167
Al, Marcie's here.

01:52.202 --> 01:55.167
Nice try, Peg,
but I'm still hungry.

01:55.202 --> 01:56.667
Where's my breakfast?

01:56.702 --> 01:58.300
The dog ate it.

01:58.335 --> 02:02.901
I see he put the pots
and pans away too.

02:02.936 --> 02:06.901
Al, I was just telling Peggy
about this great idea.

02:06.936 --> 02:09.901
You know that little hole
in your driveway,

02:09.936 --> 02:11.901
the one all the neighborhood
children splash and play in

02:11.936 --> 02:13.901
after it rains?

02:13.936 --> 02:15.501
These guys just finished
a major repaving job

02:15.536 --> 02:17.400
a couple of blocks from here.

02:17.435 --> 02:20.901
And they offered to redo both
our driveways for only $500.

02:20.936 --> 02:22.467
Isn't that great?

02:22.502 --> 02:23.968
I don't know.

02:24.003 --> 02:26.968
I tried to get Al to fix
the driveway a long time ago,

02:27.003 --> 02:28.467
But his philosophy is

02:28.502 --> 02:32.467
"Why improve a home you're
only going to live in anyway?"

02:34.167 --> 02:36.167
Al, can you think
of a better way

02:36.202 --> 02:38.033
to raise the value
of your home

02:38.068 --> 02:39.634
and save a little money
in the bargain?

02:39.669 --> 02:41.968
Sure.
Pack your bags, hon.

02:43.701 --> 02:45.701
Look they said we have
to do this right away

02:45.736 --> 02:46.701
or they'll be gone.

02:46.736 --> 02:48.400
And I think
it's a great deal.

02:48.435 --> 02:51.033
Uh-huh.
What does Steve think?

02:51.068 --> 02:53.534
Well, he's in Buffalo
at a meeting

02:53.569 --> 02:55.367
of Tellers
Against the Penny.

02:55.402 --> 02:56.767
Steve firmly believes
that the one-cent piece

02:56.802 --> 02:57.934
is a thing of the past.

02:57.969 --> 03:00.634
Well, I'm sure the feeling
is mutual.

03:00.669 --> 03:02.133
Come on, Al, make a decision.

03:02.168 --> 03:05.133
These guys are leaving
the neighborhood.

03:05.168 --> 03:06.334
Of course they're leaving
the neighborhood.

03:06.369 --> 03:07.467
These guys are crooks.

03:07.502 --> 03:08.868
First you gotta believe
they just happen

03:08.903 --> 03:10.367
to be in the neighborhood.

03:10.402 --> 03:12.501
And second, we have to believe

03:12.536 --> 03:13.868
these two guys see Marcie,

03:13.903 --> 03:15.801
and they're willing
to come back.

03:17.367 --> 03:19.400
I mean, is there
nothing so stupid

03:19.435 --> 03:21.567
that some woman
won't fall for it?

03:21.602 --> 03:23.434
I fell for you,
sweetie.

03:25.067 --> 03:26.567
How could you marry

03:26.602 --> 03:28.567
such a chauvinistic,
sexist man?

03:28.602 --> 03:29.901
A dare.

03:31.267 --> 03:32.634
Look, I'm not sexist.

03:32.669 --> 03:35.634
I'm just saying women
don't know nothing.

03:35.669 --> 03:38.667
Asphalt and finances
are male-oriented fields.

03:38.702 --> 03:43.167
Since Steve is as close
to a male as you have,

03:43.202 --> 03:45.200
he should be in
on the decision.

03:45.235 --> 03:47.567
I'll have you know
I have a degree in economics

03:47.602 --> 03:51.067
and work as a loan
officer in a bank.

03:51.102 --> 03:52.501
So if anything,
I am more qualified

03:52.536 --> 03:55.267
to make financial
decisions than you are.

03:55.302 --> 03:58.934
As good as you bankers
may be at saying,

03:58.969 --> 04:00.434
"We're sorry,
Farmer Brown,

04:00.469 --> 04:02.434
we're foreclosing.
Go sell pencils,"

04:02.469 --> 04:04.934
in this house,
I'm the boss,

04:04.969 --> 04:07.501
and I make
the financial decisions.

04:07.536 --> 04:11.334
And what a shrewd financial
decider he is too.

04:11.369 --> 04:14.501
Come on, honey.
Tell her about the time

04:14.536 --> 04:16.666
you shrewdly decided not
to buy into that property

04:16.702 --> 04:21.000
that some sucker
built the Sears Tower on.

04:21.035 --> 04:22.501
Don't forget, Peg.

04:22.536 --> 04:24.501
The money
we saved there

04:24.536 --> 04:27.501
allowed us to buy
that 2/3 acre

04:27.536 --> 04:29.000
on lake Chicamacomico.

04:29.035 --> 04:30.501
It may not look
like much now,

04:30.536 --> 04:31.701
but when they figure
out how

04:31.736 --> 04:34.501
to keep plants
and animals alive there,

04:34.536 --> 04:36.234
that's gonna be quite
a little paradise.

04:36.269 --> 04:39.934
I'll bet. But Al, I know
a good thing when I see it too.

04:39.969 --> 04:42.133
And even without you,
the deal is still a good one,

04:42.168 --> 04:43.901
and I'm going to do it.

04:43.936 --> 04:46.734
Well, you are woman.
Go out and roar.

04:48.834 --> 04:50.434
Mmm. I'm full.

04:52.567 --> 04:54.934
Peg, as usual,
every day's Thanksgiving.

04:56.634 --> 04:58.901
I'm going to work.

04:58.936 --> 05:00.534
Marce, I'll see you tonight.

05:00.569 --> 05:01.901
What for?

05:01.936 --> 05:03.300
Well, after these guys
rip you off,

05:03.335 --> 05:05.167
you'll be back
to tell me I was right.

05:05.202 --> 05:06.634
Because I will be.

05:06.669 --> 05:09.267
You're that sure of yourself?

05:09.302 --> 05:12.400
Marcie, I'd bet
my retirement property on it

05:12.435 --> 05:17.067
if the Army didn't
have it padlocked.

05:17.102 --> 05:20.200
Peggy, I cannot for the life
of me understand

05:20.235 --> 05:21.634
how you live with that man.

05:21.669 --> 05:23.801
Well, in Al's defense,

05:23.836 --> 05:27.367
what with overtime,
television, and the bathroom,

05:27.402 --> 05:29.634
I really don't
see him very much.

05:30.534 --> 05:32.467
See you later.

05:35.033 --> 05:37.767
Mom, big news down the block.

05:37.802 --> 05:40.067
The cops just arrested
these two guys

05:40.102 --> 05:42.300
trying to pull
the old asphalt scam.

05:42.335 --> 05:43.501
They what?

05:43.536 --> 05:45.100
Yeah, you know the one where
they offer

05:45.135 --> 05:46.367
to redo
your driveway real cheap,

05:46.402 --> 05:48.367
but they just use oil,

05:48.402 --> 05:51.400
so when it rains,
it all washes away.

05:51.435 --> 05:55.400
You have to be a real feeb
to fall for that one.

06:00.701 --> 06:02.167
Who are you calling?

06:02.202 --> 06:05.667
Al's mother. I told him
I'd invite her for the summer

06:05.702 --> 06:07.501
the next time he was right
about anything.

06:07.536 --> 06:09.400
Well, how do you think
he'll take it?

06:09.435 --> 06:10.467
Take what?

06:10.502 --> 06:12.267
<i>Hello?</i>

06:12.302 --> 06:15.067
My having to tell Al
he was right.

06:15.102 --> 06:18.033
You're not seriously
going to do that are you?

06:18.068 --> 06:19.133
<i>Hello?</i>

06:19.168 --> 06:21.033
Well, I have to.
He's bound to find out

06:21.068 --> 06:22.601
if he hasn't already.

06:22.636 --> 06:24.667
Marcie, let me
tell you something.

06:24.702 --> 06:26.000
<i>Peggy, is that you-?</i>

06:26.035 --> 06:29.968
In the 16 years that
I've been married to Al,

06:30.003 --> 06:31.968
I've learned there are certain
things never to ask for.

06:32.003 --> 06:35.300
<i>Never approach him for sex
during Wide World of Sports.</i>

06:35.335 --> 06:40.000
Oh, unless women's gymnastics
are on, then you got a shot.

06:40.035 --> 06:43.000
Never approach him
for sex in the morning.

06:43.035 --> 06:45.000
He thinks that
is just disgusting.

06:45.035 --> 06:47.467
And never ever
tell him he's right.

06:47.502 --> 06:48.601
Why?

06:48.636 --> 06:50.834
Because he's a man, Marcie.

06:50.869 --> 06:52.100
And the only thing uglier

06:52.135 --> 06:56.667
than a man who thinks
he's right is Al.

06:56.702 --> 06:59.534
Believe me, I know this
from experience.

06:59.569 --> 07:01.934
Let me tell you a story.

07:01.969 --> 07:03.334
A few years after
we were married

07:03.369 --> 07:06.033
I told Al that I could
hold up a fender

07:06.068 --> 07:08.167
so he could fix
the flat tire.

07:08.202 --> 07:12.033
He said, "No, let a man do it."
I said I could.

07:12.068 --> 07:14.534
So to make a long
story short,

07:14.569 --> 07:17.534
a man had to set
his leg that night.

07:17.569 --> 07:20.968
But, to this day, whenever I ask
Al to do something for me,

07:21.003 --> 07:22.167
that he doesn't want to do,

07:22.202 --> 07:24.467
he lifts up that leg
and says he can't

07:24.502 --> 07:26.467
and that it's my fault.

07:26.502 --> 07:29.467
The worst part
about it is, he's right.

07:29.502 --> 07:32.868
Marcie, don't let him
lift his leg on you.

07:40.667 --> 07:43.167
<i>Guess, I'll see you
tonight, Marce.</i>

07:43.202 --> 07:44.334
<i>What for?</i>

07:44.369 --> 07:46.267
<i>To tell me
I was right.</i>

07:46.302 --> 07:48.267
<i>You're not seriously
going to do that, are you?</i>

07:48.302 --> 07:51.334
<i>Tell me I was right.</i>

07:51.369 --> 07:52.834
<i>I was right.</i>

07:52.869 --> 07:54.367
Marcie, I'm back!

07:57.167 --> 07:58.667
Steve?

07:58.702 --> 08:02.167
I thought you weren't due back
till tomorrow night.

08:02.202 --> 08:03.534
I missed you.

08:06.701 --> 08:08.701
I'm sorry I didn't call.

08:08.736 --> 08:11.400
So you want
to fool around?

08:11.435 --> 08:13.868
Well, sure.

08:16.701 --> 08:19.067
I'm so glad to hear that.

