I haven't slept
in 18 hours.

08:35.168 --> 08:39.467
Oh, Steve's
not back yet.

08:39.501 --> 08:41.667
You have those
empty bed blues, huh?

08:41.702 --> 08:44.467
Well, yes and no.

08:44.502 --> 08:47.067
Peggy,
do you ever dream?

08:47.102 --> 08:50.367
Nah. Why dream,
when I have all this?

08:54.000 --> 08:57.000
No, I mean do you
ever have dreams?

08:57.035 --> 09:00.367
Nightmares? I had
a real doozy last night.

09:00.402 --> 09:01.868
What about?

09:01.903 --> 09:02.868
Al.

09:02.903 --> 09:04.033
Al?

09:04.068 --> 09:05.567
My Al?

09:05.602 --> 09:07.901
Yeah. See,
I was asleep-

09:07.936 --> 09:09.367
Did he have feet?

09:11.200 --> 09:12.400
Beg pardon?

09:12.435 --> 09:13.701
It's funny.

09:13.736 --> 09:16.701
In my dreams,
Al never has any feet.

09:16.736 --> 09:19.534
Oh, well. Go on.

09:19.569 --> 09:21.934
In my dream,
Steve came in

09:21.969 --> 09:27.167
and asked me if I wanted
to fool around.

09:27.202 --> 09:29.367
And when I said yes,
he turned and it was Al.

09:29.402 --> 09:30.501
My Al?

09:30.536 --> 09:32.601
Well, then what happened?

09:32.636 --> 09:33.767
Nothing.

09:33.802 --> 09:35.634
Yep, sounds like my Al.

09:38.334 --> 09:40.601
I hope you're
not upset, Peggy.

09:40.636 --> 09:43.100
About a dream?
Don't be silly.

09:43.135 --> 09:46.634
Plus, if you dreamed that
Al was in your bedroom,

09:46.669 --> 09:49.300
I should be
apologizing to you.

09:49.335 --> 09:50.334
Thanks, Peggy.

09:51.567 --> 09:54.067
Oh, but could you
do me a favor?

09:54.102 --> 09:56.534
Please don't
tell Al about this.

09:56.569 --> 09:58.033
Oh, don't worry.

09:58.068 --> 10:00.534
But could you do
something for me?

10:00.569 --> 10:03.033
If you ever dream
about Al again,

10:03.068 --> 10:06.033
could you check and see
if he has any feet?

10:06.068 --> 10:07.534
That really bothers me.

10:07.569 --> 10:08.801
Sure thing.

10:10.234 --> 10:11.734
Hi, Marce.
Hi, Peg.

10:11.769 --> 10:13.968
Bye, Peggy...Al.

10:17.901 --> 10:19.400
What's with her?

10:19.435 --> 10:22.567
She had a dream she slept
with you last night.

10:25.200 --> 10:26.567
Oh, yeah?

10:27.701 --> 10:29.067
She's a lucky gal.

10:34.534 --> 10:35.734
Marcie, I'm home.

10:37.367 --> 10:38.634
Steve?

10:38.669 --> 10:39.801
Yeah.

10:41.033 --> 10:42.467
Sorry I'm late, honey.

10:42.502 --> 10:45.467
The pro-penny people
pelted us with nickels.

10:47.534 --> 10:49.000
Did I wake you?

10:49.035 --> 10:51.334
Steve, it is you.

10:51.369 --> 10:52.834
Of course it's me.

10:52.869 --> 10:54.167
Give me a hug.

10:55.734 --> 10:57.234
Did you miss me?

10:57.269 --> 10:58.400
Mm-hmm.

10:58.435 --> 10:59.567
Don't worry.

10:59.602 --> 11:01.501
Daddy's home.

11:03.200 --> 11:06.434
And Daddy's going
to make it all better.

11:11.734 --> 11:13.367
Marcie, I'm home.

11:15.067 --> 11:19.200
Hon, you wouldn't believe
the traffic over O'Hare tonight.

11:22.334 --> 11:23.767
I swear...

11:23.802 --> 11:27.767
Someday that's where they're
going to find Amelia Earhart.

11:30.701 --> 11:31.734
But...

11:32.868 --> 11:34.534
The eagle has landed.

11:37.701 --> 11:39.634
You want to fool around?

11:52.000 --> 11:54.067
Pizza's here.

11:54.102 --> 11:57.234
Kelly, you know that's not
the way to hold a pizza.

11:57.269 --> 11:59.467
Mom, have you ever tried
to carry one of these things

11:59.502 --> 12:02.167
sitting on the back
of a Harley going 60

12:02.202 --> 12:04.267
while trying to hold
onto a fat guy

12:04.302 --> 12:06.234
who's wearing nothing
but chains and black leather.

12:06.269 --> 12:10.133
Yes, I have, and that is
not the way to do it.

12:13.767 --> 12:17.267
Mom, are we gonna do anything
different this summer?

12:17.302 --> 12:20.267
Well, Daddy got seats
for the ballgames again.

12:20.302 --> 12:21.434
Oh, puke.

12:21.469 --> 12:23.133
I thought
you liked the Cubs.

12:23.168 --> 12:25.133
I do, I just hate watching
them from the roof

12:25.168 --> 12:28.434
of that apartment building
where Dad always gets his seats.

12:28.469 --> 12:29.834
Well, honey, maybe someday
they'll forget about

12:29.869 --> 12:32.634
that fan interference call

12:32.669 --> 12:35.634
that kept the Cubs
out of the World Series

12:35.669 --> 12:38.167
and let Daddy back
into the stadium.

12:38.202 --> 12:40.367
I hope so,
because it looks so stupid

12:40.402 --> 12:43.634
with just us and the Polaskis
doing the wave.

12:52.734 --> 12:54.234
Marcie, you're a wreck.

12:54.269 --> 12:57.267
Oh, I see.

12:57.302 --> 12:58.767
Steve got back,

12:58.802 --> 13:02.767
and you two were at it
all night, huh?

13:02.802 --> 13:04.234
No.

13:04.269 --> 13:06.267
I had
that dream again...

13:06.302 --> 13:07.634
With Al.

13:10.767 --> 13:13.167
See, this is the part where
you're supposed to make a joke

13:13.202 --> 13:14.767
about Al being quick
in the sack

13:14.802 --> 13:16.167
so I can laugh
and see that

13:16.202 --> 13:17.534
you're not really mad
or anything.

13:17.569 --> 13:18.934
Marcie, that's two nights
in a row.

13:18.969 --> 13:22.100
Al hasn't been quick
in the sack with me

13:22.135 --> 13:24.667
for two nights
in a row in years.

13:24.702 --> 13:26.701
Hey, you think
I'm enjoying this?

13:26.736 --> 13:29.067
I was throwing up
all night.

13:29.102 --> 13:31.934
Well, so did I at first,
but it passes.

13:36.267 --> 13:39.100
Whatever happened to "It's only
a dream. Don't worry about it?"

13:39.135 --> 13:42.100
Peggy, can't you see what hell
my life's becoming?

13:42.135 --> 13:44.601
I haven't slept
in 48 hours.

13:44.636 --> 13:46.100
Steve's mad at me

13:46.135 --> 13:49.067
because every time
he brings up sex, I get sick.

13:49.102 --> 13:51.033
And now you're
yelling at me.

13:51.068 --> 13:52.534
And why not?

13:52.569 --> 13:55.501
You're the one dreaming
around with my husband.

13:55.536 --> 13:57.334
Hey, Peg.

13:57.369 --> 13:58.367
Ha!

14:00.534 --> 14:01.767
Hey, Marce.

14:05.067 --> 14:07.634
I tell you,
what a day.

14:13.267 --> 14:16.267
All day long,
it's pick up the shoes.

14:16.302 --> 14:19.267
Put down the shoes.
Pick up the shoes.

14:19.302 --> 14:22.767
Tomorrow ought to be
a good day for you.

14:22.802 --> 14:24.767
Tomorrow
I wash the car...

14:24.802 --> 14:26.634
in my t-shirt.

14:27.934 --> 14:31.601
I can't believe
you told him.

14:31.636 --> 14:33.467
I can't believe
you dream about him.

14:33.502 --> 14:35.467
I can't believe
everybody doesn't.

14:38.100 --> 14:39.834
I'm mortified.

14:39.869 --> 14:41.200
Well, get happy.

14:47.801 --> 14:50.734
Well, Peg, it looks
like another little filly

14:50.769 --> 14:52.601
in the old
Bundy stable.

14:53.734 --> 14:55.534
Get me a beer, will ya?

14:55.569 --> 14:58.167
Al, what are you doing
in Marcie's dream?

14:58.202 --> 15:00.534
Ruining her
for all other men.

15:02.501 --> 15:05.200
You are doing something
to cause those dreams.

15:05.235 --> 15:08.200
Now I don't know what it is,
but I want you to cut it out.

15:08.235 --> 15:10.501
I'll cut it out, Peg,
just tell me what to do.

15:10.536 --> 15:12.334
What should I do,
stop wearing t-shirts?

15:12.369 --> 15:16.000
Stop oozing sex
from every pore?

15:16.035 --> 15:19.267
That isn't sex, Al.

15:19.302 --> 15:21.300
What should I do, Peg?

15:21.335 --> 15:23.300
Well, you could
come upstairs

15:23.335 --> 15:26.300
and be my dreamlover
for a while.

15:26.335 --> 15:27.801
Peg, not tonight.

15:27.836 --> 15:30.167
This leg has
been acting up.

15:31.767 --> 15:34.601
Ever since that night
with the car...

15:34.636 --> 15:35.667
Fine, fine.

15:35.702 --> 15:37.100
Then let's discuss
who else's dreams

15:37.135 --> 15:40.100
you've been
gallivanting around in.

15:40.135 --> 15:42.601
Perhaps Mrs. Pritchard
across the street.

15:42.636 --> 15:46.601
I've seen how she looks
at you over her walker.

15:46.636 --> 15:48.400
If you think...

